[Information about person-place-time is scarce. What is the age group affected? All the same sex? What is the spatial distribution of cases? What is the epidemiological link between them? Was there complete resolution of symptoms? How soon?

Although the news report mentions that "the hypothesis of poisoning by external factors" has been discarded, there is information that the results of chromatographic analysis of water samples are still awaited. Therefore, the hypothesis of poisoning should still be considered plausible.

Additional information on the results of the investigation would be welcome. - Mod.RNA

Maps of Brazil can be seen at http://s13.postimg.org/jumnalk87/map_of_Brazil.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2887326,34678. The municipalities of Itapira and Mogi Mirim can be located on the map of Sao Paulo state at http://www.copesp.org/images/mapaspg.jpg (eastern part of administrative region 5). - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

